Here's a copy of the email that went out regarding the Dagstuhl report. Ms6ep 16:35, 27 January 2007 (EST)

Hi folks, We will be discussing the Dagstuhl report in class on Tuesday. The report has been assigned as reading for homework. To facilitate the class discussion, I would like each student to pick a different Working Group summary and be prepared to talk about the working group. We will be using the class wiki to assign working groups. You should be receiving an email with a username and password to logon to the wiki. Then pick your favorite working group that is still available (first come, first serve). Since there are eight working groups and nine students, two students may pair up for one of the working groups. Within your working group, you should identify (a) the motivation for the research area, and (b) the research challenges in this area. Your summary will only consume at most 5 minutes of class time (per person), so you should have enough time between now and Tuesday to prepare.
